---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="FAQ - Bibles & Jiu Jitsu"
  description="Find answers to common questions about our Bible study and No-Gi Jiu Jitsu sessions in Austin. Learn about attire, experience requirements, session format, and more. Everyone is welcome to join or observe."
>
  <div class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">What should I wear?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            For the Jiu Jitsu portion, wear a rash guard or close fitting t-shirt and athletic
            shorts suitable for grappling. For Bible study, the same attire is fine. Don't forget to
            bring your Bible if you have one!
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Do I need any experience?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            No experience is required! Whether you're new to Jiu Jitsu, Bible study, or both, you're
            welcome to join us. Our community is open to all skill levels.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Is there a cost to attend?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Our fellowship is completely free. We believe in making this unique combination of
            spiritual and physical growth accessible to everyone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">What's the format of a typical session?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Each session includes No-Gi Jiu Jitsu instruction, followed by Bible study and
            fellowship time. The environment is welcoming and supportive, focusing on both physical
            and spiritual growth.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Where do you meet?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            We meet at Renzo Gracie Round Rock, located at 2051 Gattis School Rd, Ste 900, Round
            Rock, TX 78664. The facility is clean, spacious, and perfect for our combined
            activities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Can I just observe first?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Absolutely! You're welcome to come and observe both the Jiu Jitsu and Bible study
            portions before participating. It's a great way to get comfortable with our format.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
